			<div class="faq__lg__body">
				Semaglutide is a GLP-1 receptor agonist, which mimics a hormone that
				helps regulate blood sugar levels, slow down digestion, and reduce
				appetite. Tirzepatide, on the other hand, is a dual GIP and GLP-1
				receptor agonist, meaning it mimics two hormones that regulate blood
				sugar and appetite. This dual action can make weight loss programs with
				injections more effective. By combining two hormonal effects,
				Tirzepatide enhances the benefits of weight loss programs with
				injections, offering better blood sugar control and greater weight loss
				compared to using GLP-1 alone.
			</div>
